# Introduction
`pd-markdown-mode` is my attempt at a markdown mode the works the way
I want.

It targets the markdown with [Pandoc] extensions.

It provides outline style editing.

It provides indentation and filling.

- Pandoc and Hakyll style header blocks.

# Markdown elements 
## Block
- Paragraph
- Indented code
- Delimited code.
- Lists
- Tables
- Horizontal rules.
- Block-quotes
- Meta data header (Pandoc and Hakyll style)
- Comments

## Spans
- Verbatim
- Emphasis
- Strong Emphasis
- Strikeout
- TeX maths

## Links
- Links, inline and reference
- Footnotes
- Images
- Citations

## Lists
- Numbered lists
- Plain lists
- Number examples
- Description lists

# Indentation
- Headers always to column 0.
- Body text to line up with previous line.

